channel.title: My real life drawings
channel.description:
note: almost all of these were drawn during school (usually the notebook paper ones) and most are about a year old.
Here is a robot i drew up when i was bored, notice the leaf :P [img]http://img403.imageshack.us/img403/7115/robotirlfq0.png[/img]
Here is a pistol i drew, at my old school we were aloud to draw guns.. [img]http://img89.imageshack.us/img89/7634/pistolirlfc4.png[/img]
Chucky plz? [img]http://img512.imageshack.us/img512/2361/chuckyzy2.png[/img]
Decided to get into mange a lil' bit [img]http://img120.imageshack.us/img120/9575/mangabj2.png[/img]
here is a baby's face, i didnt look at any relatives or anything to draw the people [img]http://img80.imageshack.us/img80/5848/babyirlyw3.png[/img]
here is a random girl i drew, i usually never finish to get to the second eye, and its not that good :( [img]http://img329.imageshack.us/img329/4405/randomgirlop7.png[/img]
My kittie Kats :) so many girls wanted a copy of it :rolleyes: [img]http://img213.imageshack.us/img213/17/kittiesev2.png[/img]

item.title: My real life drawings
item.dc:creator: @Frell Frell
item.description:
@Frell wrote:

[quote=“OmidSan, post:22, topic:190110”][quote author=exe626 link=topic=253131.msg2120774#msg2120774 date=1205972002]
I agree with Frell. Even if you plan to color an image, never do it with the original. Trace it to a rougher piece of paper and test out color schemes, different techniques and different styles. Coloring is the hardest part of any piece of art, a simple mistake is all you need to do to have it rejected in the professional world.
[/quote]
It really is, that’s why many artists don’t bother coloring. [br][br][size=1]Posted on: March 19, 2008, 02:35:20 PM[/size][hr][quote author=Frell link=topic=253131.msg2120951#msg2120951 date=1205976197]

I agree with Frell

That is the second time anyone has said that to me

I just dont like coloring, shading looks very origional and more real, you cant really capture light with coloring pencils
[/quote]
Lol aha.
Yes u can capture light with coloring pencils…[/quote]
Not really, sometimes it just looks like spots you forgot to color.

Read full topic
